When it 's time for their biannual powwow , the nation 's manufacturing titans typically jet off to the sunny confines of resort towns like [LOC Boca Raton] and [LOC Hot Springs] . 
Not this year . 
[ORG The National Association of Manufacturers] settled on the [MISC Hoosier] capital of [LOC Indianapolis] for its fall board meeting . 
And the city decided to treat its guests more like royalty or rock stars than factory owners . 
The idea , of course : to prove to 125 corporate decision makers that the buckle on the [ORG Rust Belt] is n't so rusty after all , that it 's a good place for a company to expand . 
On the receiving end of the message were officials from giants like [LOC Du Pont] and [ORG Maytag] , along with lesser knowns like [ORG Trojan Steel] and the [ORG Valley Queen Cheese Factory] . 
For starters , the executives joined Mayor [PER William H. Hudnut III] for an evening of the [LOC Indianapolis Symphony Orchestra] and a guest pianist - comedian [PER Victor Borge] . 
Champagne and dessert followed . 
The next morning , with a police escort , busloads of executives and their wives raced to the [ORG Indianapolis Motor Speedway] , unimpeded by traffic or red lights . 
The governor could n't make it , so the lieutenant governor welcomed the special guests . 
A buffet breakfast was held in the museum , where food and drinks are banned to everyday visitors . 
Then , in the guests ' honor , the speedway hauled out four drivers , crews and even the official [LOC Indianapolis] 500 announcer for a 10 - lap exhibition race . 
After the race , [ORG Fortune 500] executives drooled like schoolboys over the cars and drivers . 
No dummies , the drivers pointed out they still had space on their machines for another sponsor 's name or two . 
Back downtown , the execs squeezed in a few meetings at the hotel before boarding the buses again . 
This time , it was for dinner and dancing -- a block away . 
Under the stars and moons of the renovated [LOC Indiana] Roof ballroom , nine of the hottest chefs in town fed them [LOC Indiana] duckling mousseline , lobster consomme , veal mignon and chocolate terrine with a raspberry sauce . 
Knowing a tasty -- and free -- meal when they eat one , the executives gave the chefs a standing ovation . 
More than a few CEOs say the red - carpet treatment tempts them to return to a heartland city for future meetings . 
But for now , they 're looking forward to their winter meeting -- [LOC Boca] in February . 
[LOC South Korea] registered a trade deficit of $ 101 million in October , reflecting the country 's economic sluggishness , according to government figures released Wednesday . 
Preliminary tallies by the [ORG Trade and Industry Ministry] showed another trade deficit in October , the fifth monthly setback this year , casting a cloud on [LOC South Korea] 's export - oriented economy . 
Exports in October stood at $ 5.29 billion , a mere 0.7 % increase from a year earlier , while imports increased sharply to $ 5.39 billion , up 20 % from last October . 
[LOC South Korea] 's economic boom , which began in 1986 , stopped this year because of prolonged labor disputes , trade conflicts and sluggish exports . 
Government officials said exports at the end of the year would remain under a government target of $ 68 billion . 
Despite the gloomy forecast , [LOC South Korea] has recorded a trade surplus of $ 71 million so far this year . 
From January to October , the nation 's accumulated exports increased 4 % from the same period last year to $ 50.45 billion . 
Imports were at $ 50.38 billion , up 19 % . 
[ORG Newsweek] , trying to keep pace with rival Time magazine , announced new advertising rates for 1990 and said it will introduce a new incentive plan for advertisers . 
The new ad plan from [ORG Newsweek] , a unit of the [ORG Washington Post Co.] , is the second incentive plan the magazine has offered advertisers in three years . 
Plans that give advertisers discounts for maintaining or increasing ad spending have become permanent fixtures at the news weeklies and underscore the fierce competition between [ORG Newsweek] , [ORG Time Warner Inc] . 's Time magazine , and [PER Mortimer B. Zuckerman] 's [ORG U.S. News & World Report] . 
[PER Alan Spoon] , recently named [ORG Newsweek] president , said [ORG Newsweek] 's ad rates would increase 5 % in January . 
A full , four - color page in Newsweek will cost $ 100,980 . 
When the [LOC Soviet Union] collapsed in 1991 , partisans of [PER Ronald Reagan] claimed he had " won " the cold war . 
Although a careful review of the facts will show it was not true , the claim was that the [LOC Soviet Union] became overextended attempting to keep up with [PER Ray-gun] 's defense spending . 
[PER Pappy Bush] , who was the president at the time , claimed that he had won the cold war since the collapse of the [LOC Soviet Union] happened on his watch . 
Regardless of how one views those claims , for many people -- capitalists especially -- heralded the " victory " of capitalism . 
