International ; Government ; Telecom ; technology ; science 
[ORG NATO] CONSIDERS cyber attacks a threat to military and civilian computer networks after the [MISC Estonian] Government was struck by cyber attacks in 2007 . 
[ORG NATO] allies have signed an agreement to fund a research center to bolster defenses against cyber attacks . 
On 14 May 2008 7 [ORG NATO] allies signed an agreement to fund a research center . 
The center will bolster [ORG NATO] 's defenses against cyber attacks . 
The center will be operational in August 2008 . 
The center will formally open in 2009 . 
A staff of 30 specialists will conduct research and training on cyber warfare . 
[ORG NATO] CONSIDERS cyber attacks a growing threat to military and civilian computer networks . 
The research center is based in [LOC Tallinn] , [LOC Estonia] . 
Defense chiefs from [LOC Estonia] , [LOC Latvia] , [LOC Lithuania] , [LOC Germany] , [LOC Italy] , [LOC Spain] and [LOC Slovakia] signed the agreement . 
The agreement will provide staff and funding for the research center . 
In 2007 the [MISC Estonian] Government was struck by cyber attacks . 
The cyber attacks crippled government and corporate computer networks . 
The cyber attacks were unprecedented . 
The cyber attacks followed a dispute over the relocation of a [MISC Soviet] war memorial in [LOC Estonia] 's capital . 
Many suspect the [LOC Kremlin] of the cyber attacks . 
[LOC Russia] denied involvement with the cyber attacks . 
[ORG NATO] 's top commander in charge of military modernization [LOC U.S.] Gen. [PER James Mattis] stated -- 
[ORG NATO] will cooperate to bring together the best minds together in cyber defense . 
[ORG NATO] cannot say that [ORG NATO] will not defend the web that everybody needs . 
The [LOC U.S.] will join the project as an observer . 
Other [ORG NATO] nations may join the project later . 
At a news conference at the research center [MISC Estonian] Defense Minister [PER Jaak Aaviksoo] stated that -- 
Cyber space essentially has no borders . 
It is difficult to defend the sovereignty of land and sea borders and air space . 
It is even more complicated in borderless cyber space where there is no smoking gun , fingerprints or footprints . 
The agreement was signed during a regular meeting of [ORG Chiefs of Defense] Staff from the 26 [ORG NATO] allies . 
[LOC Estonia] is a [MISC Baltic] nation . 
