Tantalum can be used in the production of chemical processing equipment , nuclear reactors and missile parts and is subject to export restrictions under [MISC Russian] law . 
Tantalum powder is a super-grade chemical and can be used in the manufacture of mobile phones , personal computers , motor vehicles and electronics goods . 
Prosecutors have stated that [PER Godzhayev] lied about the contents of an outgoing shipment in customs documents after a business partner asked [PER Godzhayev] to send more than a ton of materials containing tantalum to [LOC Iran] in July 2007 . 
Godzhayev was detained after customs officials checked the shipment in a container on a boat due to leave for [LOC Iran] . 
Godzhayev is a citizen of [LOC Uzbekistan] and could face trial soon . 
Godzhayev could be sentenced to 7 years in prison if convicted . 
Godzhayev is being held in [LOC Astrakhan] . 
[PER Godzhayev] and [PER Godzhayev] 's lawyers were not immediately available to comment . 
The [MISC Russian] government support [LOC Iran] 's right to nuclear energy and is building [LOC Iran] 's first nuclear power plant . 
The [MISC Russian] government has stated there is no evidence proving claims by the [LOC U.S.] and other [MISC Western] countries that the [MISC Iranian] government is seeking to develop nuclear weapons . 
Officials in [LOC Moscow] are involved in international efforts to persuade the [MISC Iranian] government to ease fears by abandoning uranium enrichment . 
The [MISC Russian] government has also questioned [LOC U.S.] assessments of the potential threat from [MISC Iranian] missiles . 
[MISC Russian] and [LOC United States] leaders have maintained cooperation in efforts to thwart the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction . 
2008-07-28 
[LOC Afghanistan] ( AF ) 
Narcotics ; international 
A [ORG U.N.] representative stated that the conversion of opium resin into heroin is increasingly being done inside [LOC Afghanistan] but that the chemicals needed to complete the conversion are being smuggled into [LOC Afghanistan] from other countries . 
The [ORG U.N.] representative requested the international community share more information on known smugglers of the chemicals . 
The [ORG U.N.] stated on 28 July 2008 that the international community should do more to stop chemicals used to convert opium to heroin from reaching [LOC Afghanistan] and detailed increasing sophistication in [LOC Afghanistan] 's drug trade . 
[LOC Afghanistan] produces more than 90 percent of the world 's opium . 
Opium production in [LOC Afghanistan] has increased since the [MISC U.S.] -led invasion removed the [ORG Taliban] regime in 2001 . 
Officials in the [MISC American] -backed government and [ORG Taliban] militants are believed to profit from the illicit trade . 
[ORG U.N.] figures show [LOC Afghanistan] yielded approximately 9000 tons of opium in 2007 which could create more than 900 tons of heroin . 
[LOC Afghanistan] 's representative for the [ORG U.N. Office] on Drugs and Crime [PER Christina Oguz] stated the conversion of opium resin into heroin is increasingly being done inside [LOC Afghanistan] mostly at laboratories in the border regions in the insurgency-plagued [LOC South] and the [LOC East .] 
[LOC Oguz] stated to reporters in [LOC Kabul] that evidence of higher quality [MISC Afghan] heroin indicates that the people running the labs are getting assistance from chemists who have come from outside the country as foreign consultants . 
[LOC Oguz] stated the chemists originated from countries near the border but did not detail specific countries . 
[LOC Oguz] stated the chemicals needed to make the heroin were being smuggled from [LOC China] , [LOC South Korea] , [MISC European] countries , including [LOC Russia] , and other parts of the world . 
[LOC Oguz] stated the so-called precursor chemicals such as acetic anhydride also have legal uses including in the paint and pharmaceutical industries . 
[LOC Oguz] stated the chemicals often are legally exported but later diverted to [LOC Afghanistan] for illicit goals and [LOC Afghanistan] has no major legal industries that would require such chemicals . 
[LOC Oguz] stated -- 
Blaming [LOC Afghanistan] alone for the heroin problem in the world is not correct . 
[LOC Afghanistan] does produce the opium which is the raw material for heroin but it is not possible to make heroin without certain chemicals that are not produced inside [LOC Afghanistan] and are smuggled into [LOC Afghanistan] . 
More than 200 tons of the chemicals have been seized by [MISC Afghan] authorities since 2006 but some 13000 tons were needed based on 2007 's opium production figures . 
The figures suggest the confiscated amount represented a small fraction of the total smuggled in . 
Most seizures of the chemicals occur along the eastern border with [LOC Pakistan] but a good deal comes via the western border with [LOC Iran] . 
[LOC Oguz] stated the international community should share more information on known smugglers of the chemicals who were long-established and based in [LOC Afghanistan] 's neighboring countries . 
[MISC Western] officials are increasingly concerned that [ORG Taliban] militants are bankrolling the insurgency through the drug trade . 
The [ORG U.N.] briefing comes in the wake of allegations that [MISC Afghan] President [PER Hamid Karzai] protected drug lords for political reasons . 
A former senior [ORG U.S. State Department] counter-narcotics official wrote in an article in the 27 July 2008 issue of [ORG New York Times] magazine that narco-corruption went to the top of the [MISC Afghan] Government . 
The official alleged [ORG Karzai] was reluctant to move against big drug lords in [ORG Karzai] 's political power base in the south of [LOC Afghanistan] where most opium is produced . 
[PER Karzai] has stated commitment to eliminating corruption and battling the drug trade . 
[LOC Oguz] stated on 28 July 2008 that corruption exists within the system but [LOC Afghanistan] lacked a well-trained police force for many years and officials are only now taking steps in fighting corruption . 
