The ruling conflicts with a [ORG United Nations] anti-terror order obliging [ORG United Nations] Member States to freeze assets of people and entities suspected of funding terror groups . 
[ORG The European Union] 's highest court also stated that the [ORG United Nations] order failed to offer individuals on a terror blacklist or individuals on the defense any legal rights to a judicial review under [MISC European] law . 
[ORG The European Union] 's highest court acknowledged that the reasons for freezing the assets of [PER Yasin Al-Qadi] and the [ORG Al-Barakaat International Foundation] may be justified . 
It is not known whether [ORG European Union] nations which have set up a joint terror blacklist will unfreeze the assets . 
None of the groups have so far been officially removed from the blacklist because [ORG European Union] Governments argue the court rulings do not oblige the [ORG European Union] nations to remove the names from the list but only force the [ORG European Union] to inform the individuals and groups on the list that the assets have been frozen . 
Head of the [ORG Saudi] -based [MISC Muwafaq Foundation] [PER Yasin Al-Qadi] appealed against the [ORG European Union] 's decision to freeze proprietary assets . 
[LOC United States] Treasury officials allege the [ORG Muwafaq Foundation] is an al-Qaida Front used to funnel millions of dollars and euros to al-Qaida . 
[ORG Al-Barakaat International] appealed the [ORG European Union] 's decision to freeze 1 million [MISC Swedish] kroner or 152247 [LOC United States] dollars . 
