[PER Thomas Olsson] also stated that the lawyers for [ORG Al-Barakaat International] have to examine the judicial consequences of the verdict as the sanctions remain on a [ORG United Nations] level . 
[ORG The European Union] 's highest court stated on September 3 , 2008 that the 27-nation [ORG European Union] is required to inform any person whose assets are being frozen why as swiftly as possible after the decision is taken in order to allow the person with frozen assets the right to legal recourse . 
[MISC Swedish] lawyer [PER Thomas Olsson] who represented [PER Al-Barakaat] in the case approved of the ruling . 
This ruling may hinder international efforts to stop the financing of terror groups including al-Qaida . 
The ruling overturns an earlier 2005 [ORG European Union] court decision that rejected the appeals of [PER Al-Qadi] and the [MISC Al-Barakaat] international foundation . 
The ruling stated that the lower [ORG European Union] 's court judgment erred in law by stating that [ORG European Union] courts had no jurisdiction to review the legality of the contested order to freeze assets of individuals and groups deemed to be funding terror groups by the [ORG United Nations] . 
Other suspects and groups on an [ORG European Union] terror blacklist have also won legal victories for similar reasons against being listed . 
These suspects and groups have so far not had assets unfrozen or names removed from the [ORG European Union] 's blacklist . 
[ORG The] [ORG European Union] 's High Court had previously overturned an [ORG European Union] decision to freeze the assets of the People 's [LOC Mujahadeen of] [LOC Iran] . 
[ORG The People 's Mujahadeen of] [LOC Iran] is an exiled [MISC Iranian] Resistance movement that is on the [ORG European Union] 's terror blacklist . 
