terrorism ; international ; government 
An institute for public policy research report said there are 27 weak states that pose a threat to [LOC Britain] 's national security as the States could provide bases for terrorists . 
The report stated [MISC British] government must help to stabilize weak states and push for international regulations . 
A report published on 27 November 2008 stated [LOC Britain] is vulnerable to terrorists operating out of weak States where terrorists can run training camps and raise funds undetected . 
The report was co-authored by former [ORG NATO] chief [PER George Robertson] and published by international think tank the [ORG Institute for Public Policy Research] . 
The report said there are 27 weak states that pose a threat to [LOC Britain] 's national security as the States could provide bases for terrorists . 
The countries include [LOC Haiti] , [LOC Nigeria] , [LOC Somalia] and [LOC Yemen] and have vulnerable Governments that are unwilling or unable to control the territories . 
The report 's authors stated criminal groups that fund terrorist organizations through drug trafficking and manufacturing counterfeit goods can operate in weak States without being detected . 
Terrorists who raise funds in these [ORG States] could then coordinate an attack on [LOC Britain] . 
The report stated transnational terrorists have discovered that the global space is largely unregulated with the rule of law either weak or nonexistent and is a place where terrorists can operate with a reasonable prospect of impunity as in the mountains of [LOC Afghanistan] before 9/11 . 
Deputy Director of the ippr and 1 of the report 's authors [PER Ian] kearns stated terrorists could run camps in remote areas which Governments rarely monitor . 
[LOC Kearns] referenced terrorist training camps in the [LOC Sahel] which is a region of [LOC sub-Saharan Africa] that runs though several countries including [LOC Mali] , [LOC Chad] and [LOC Sudan] . 
[LOC Kearns] stated that these remote areas are impossible to patrol and any activity could go undetected . 
The report stated [MISC British] government must help to stabilize weak states and push for international regulations that would stop terrorists using freely available information to create and unleash new forms of biological warfare such as a modified version of the influenza virus . 
[LOC Kearns] stated the Government must take a multilateral approach to areas including biotechnology but that the government is not moving quickly enough on the approach . 
[LOC Kearns] stated the global financial crisis shows the results of not having multilateral frameworks in place to deal with international issues . 
