[LOC China] ( [ORG CN] ) 
International ; military ; weapons ; space ; technology ; government 
[LOC China] confirmed on January 23 , 2007 after 12 days of silence that [LOC China] had fired a guided missile into space to destroy one of its satellites . 
The test caused protests from the [LOC United States] and other nations . 
[LOC China] confirmed on January 23 , 2007 after 12 days of silence that [LOC China] had fired a guided missile into space to destroy one of its satellites . 
The test caused protests from the [LOC United States] and other nations . 
[ORG Foreign Ministry] spokesman [PER Liu Jianchao] said the [LOC United States] and other Governments have now been informed about the secret test through diplomatic channels . 
[PER Liu Jianchao] stated that the use of anti-satellite technology does not mean [LOC China] has abandoned its long-standing opposition to the military use of space . 
[PER Liu Jianchao] said at a ministry briefing that the test was not targeted against any country and does not pose a threat to any country . 
[PER Liu Jianchao] said that no plans for another such test by the secretive [MISC Chinese] military . 
The [MISC Chinese] test shot destroyed an overage weather satellite 537 miles above [LOC Earth] and was detected by [LOC U.S.] monitors January 11 , 2007 . 
The [MISC Chinese] government refused to discuss it . 
The test raised concern in the [LOC United States] . 
Officials and analysts interpreted it as a signal that [LOC U.S.] military satellites could be vulnerable to attack by [LOC China] . 
[LOC China] 's ability to shoot down satellites could pose an added threat in the event of hostilities over [LOC Taiwan] because the [LOC U.S.] military relies on satellites for reconnaissance , navigation , weapons guidance systems and anti-missile defenses . 
[LOC China] 's newly demonstrated ability could threaten [MISC Taiwanese] satellites monitoring [MISC Chinese] short- and medium-range missile deployments along the [LOC Taiwan] Strait . 
[LOC U.S.] officials were dismayed by the [MISC Chinese] test because the [LOC United States] and [LOC Russia] have abstained from such tests after testing anti-satellite technology in the 1980s . 
This decision was partly because destroying satellites creates debris that could damage satellites in nearby orbits . 
[PER Liu] declined to address questions on this danger . 
Experts estimate that several hundred thousand debris fragments were created by the destruction of the satellite . 
The satellite orbited in a section of space where 125 other satellites fly . 
[LOC China] has started an accelerated military modernization program and has repeatedly stated its desire to be able to compete in 21st-century warfare . 
This includes the use of advanced electronics and information systems . 
The [MISC Chinese] military runs [LOC China] 's space program and has identified space-based communications and sensing systems as key to such efforts . 
Some [MISC Chinese] military theorists have advocated asymmetrical warfare . 
Pinpoint weapons would be used to disrupt the more advanced and better-equipped [LOC U.S.] military . 
Analysts believed that the January 11 , 2007 test was part of the military modernization program despite [LOC China] 's frequent declarations that it wants to prevent an arms race in space . 
[PER Liu] repeated the long-standing [MISC Chinese] position when asked about the appearance of a contradiction and said [LOC China] will further promote de-weaponization and the peaceful use of outer space . 
[LOC China] has consistently advocated at the [ORG United Nations] for the peaceful development of space and pushed for an international agreement to prevent it from becoming the theater for a new arms race . 
The [LOC United States] has opposed [LOC China] 's suggestion for an international conference to pursue such an accord and argued there is no need for it . 
[PER Liu] was asked whether the anti-satellite test violated the spirit of [LOC China] 's proclaimed position and why [LOC China] kept silent for nearly two weeks while officials around the world were discussing it on the basis of [LOC U.S.] intelligence reports . 
[PER Liu] said [LOC China] has nothing to hide . 
[LOC China] made the response about the test quickly after the relevant parties expressed their concerns . 
[LOC China] stressed that opposition of weaponization and an arms race in outer space . 
[LOC China] 's position has not changed . 
