The [ORG interior ministry] said [MISC Saudi] police have arrested 10 men and accused them of collecting donations to fund terrorist acts outside the Kingdom . 
A lawyer and a prominent dissident said that at least seven of the men were [MISC Saudi] democracy activists whose arrest was a government attempt to abort their civic rights work . 
The [ORG interior ministry] said [MISC Saudi] police have arrested 10 men and accused them of collecting donations to fund terrorist acts outside the Kingdom . 
A lawyer and a prominent dissident said that at least seven of the men were [MISC Saudi] democracy activists whose arrest was a government attempt to abort their civic rights work . 
Matrouk al-Faleh said the seven men had been waiting for government approval to set up a civic rights group . 
The men were mostly of them lawyers and professors . 
Al-Faleh was jailed in 2004 for calling for more democracy in the kingdom . 
The men had planned to present authorities with a list of more than 40 prisoners without legal representation whom they intended to defend . 
[ORG Al-Faleh] said the terrorist allegation is a cover-up and that it was used to get al-Faleh arrested . 
This is an attempt to abort the civic rights work the authorities were planning . 
Police went to the [LOC Jiddah] beach house of lawyer [PER Essam basrawi] on Friday night and arrested [PER basrawi] and five other [MISC Saudi] men . 
[PER Bassim Alim] said [MISC Saudi] businessman [PER Abdul-Aziz Al-khereiji] was arrested at a checkpoint as [PER Al-khereiji] drove with his wife to [LOC Jiddah] . 
[PER Alim] is the attorney who represents four of the detainees . 
[PER Basrawi] 's [MISC Moroccan] personal assistant also was detained . 
There was no information on the identities of the two other men . 
An [ORG interior ministry] spokesman told local newspapers that the arrested men had been involved in financing recruiters who sign up young [MISC Saudis] to go into turbulent areas . 
That is generally a reference to [LOC Iraq] . 
The spokesman said sizable amounts of cash had been found during searches of the men 's homes . 
Many young [MISC Saudi] radicals have crossed the long and porous border between the [LOC Kingdom] and [LOC Iraq] and joined up with [MISC Sunni Muslim] insurgents there . 
[PER Alim] said that the government 's accusations were baseless and that his clients were well-known reformists with no connection to terrorism . 
[PER Alim] said the men might have been raising funds for [MISC Palestinian] or [MISC Iraqi] refugees . 
The men had been warned repeatedly by the government not to gather or write petitions because authorities feared the rise of a new political reform movement . 
[PER Alim] said the men do not want any kind of organized reform movement . 
The men are trying to stop any organized calls for reform . 
[PER Alim] said police had illegally searched the men 's homes without warrants and seized files , books and computers . 
This was after midnight on February 2 , 2002 . 
Neither [PER Alim] nor family members have been allowed to see the arrested men . 
Faleh did not know why they were not allowed lawyers or charged publicly or shown proof or evidence if they are guilty of the crime . 
The arrests were the first to target democracy activists since reform-minded King [PER Abdullah] took the throne in 2005 and pardoned [PER Faleh] and two other leading activists who had spent 18 months in prison . 
A dozen other men arrested with them in March 2004 signed statements pledging to stop lobbying for political freedoms . 
Faleh and the two others refused to sign and demanded legal representation and a public trial . 
[ORG Legal Defense] and public trials are allowed under [MISC Saudi] law but rarely applied . 
Most defendants go to court without attorneys . 
[LOC Saudi Arabia] is an absolute monarchy and has a consultative council appointed by the government . 
It carried out limited municipal elections in 2005 . 
[MISC The Kingdom] continues to show little tolerance for political opposition despite slow progression toward reform from [PER Abdullah] . 
It imposes strict limits on freedom of expression and bans public gatherings and political parties . 
[PER Sulaiman Al-Rushoodi] is a lawyer and former judge who had been among the group of activists detained in 2004 . 
[PER Al-Rushoodi] was one of the men arrested on February 2 , 2002 . 
Al-Rushoodi was released several weeks later after pledging to address his demands solely to authorities . 
[PER Al-Rushoodi] joined the defense team of three activists still behind bars . 
Basrawi is a prominent activist who helped draft petitions addressed to the Government during a vibrant period of political activism before the 2004 arrests 
The [ORG Consultative Shura Council] recently announced it was considering laws permitting the setting up of civic rights groups which are currently not allowed in the [LOC Kingdom] . 
[LOC Saudi Arabia] has two Government-appointed human rights committees but bans independent human and civil rights organizations . 
