International ; Telecom ; business ; space ; Government ; technology 
[LOC China] has built and launched a communications satellite for [LOC Nigeria] . 
The satellite demonstrate 's [LOC China] 's increasing skill in space technology . 
[MISC Chinese] officials stated on May 14 , 2007 that [LOC China] had launched a [MISC Chinese] manufactured communications satellite into orbit on behalf of [LOC Nigeria] . 
[MISC Chinese] officials stated that the geostationary satellite will provide communications services over [LOC Africa] and parts of the [LOC Middle East] and [LOC Southern Europe] . 
The [MISC Chinese] officials also stated that the satellite will go into operation by the end of 2007 and is expected to last 15 years . 
The satellite will be managed from a control station in [LOC Abuja] , [LOC Nigeria] . 
This launch marks the first time [LOC China] has built a commercial satellite and put the satellite into orbit on contract for another country . 
The launch occurred on May 14 , 2007 before dawn near the [LOC Xichang] space center in southwestern [LOC Sichuan] province . 
Some view the launch as another sign of [LOC China] 's increasing skill in space technology and [LOC China] 's determination to be among the world 's great powers seeking to utilize the reaches of outer space for benefits on earth . 
[LOC China] 's space program 's rapid progress has caused worries in the [LOC United States] because the program is run by the military and [LOC China] has been recently emphasizing space-based information warfare . 
The concern intensified following the successful January 11 , 2007 test-firing of an anti-satellite missile . 
Some analysts stated that the test-firing demonstrated a risk to the many satellites on which [LOC United States] military forces rely for navigation and weapons guidance . 
[LOC China] 's space agency sent 2 astronauts into orbit in October 2005 in the [ORG Agency] 's second manned spaceflight . 
The [MISC Chinese] government on May 7 , 2007 adopted a 10 year plan for expanded space exploration . 
The plan includes more manned flights as well as unmanned probes of the [LOC Moon] and beyond . 
[MISC Chinese] officials stated that the launch of the nigcomsat-1 aboard a [MISC Long] March 3 B rocket on May 14 , 2007 represented a commercial challenge . 
Some saw the launch as a symbol of [LOC China] 's broad network of economic relations with [LOC Africa] . 
The official [ORG New China News Agency] stated that the satellite represents [LOC China] 's wish to cooperate with developing countries in the peaceful use of outer space and to promote a closer relationship between [LOC China] and [MISC African] countries . 
[LOC Nigeria] 's managing director of the nigcomsat-1 project [PER Hammed Rufai] stated that the launch was a breakthrough in ending the exclusive reliance on oil because the satellite will help [LOC Nigeria] move toward knowledge-based industries . 
The official [ORG New China News Agency] stated that [LOC China] secured the 311 million dollar contract in 2004 in a bidding process in which 21 other companies took part . 
President of the [ORG Great Wall Industry Corporation] [PER Wang Haibo] stated that the [MISC Nigerian] contract puts [LOC China] onto the short list of countries that can build , launch and maintain a satellite for other nations . 
[MISC Chinese] officials stated that about 30 similar contracts have been signed for future launches . 
In the 1990s [LOC China] frequently launched satellites for other countries after the satellites were manufactured elsewhere and acquired a reputation for providing such services more cheaply than other launch-capable countries . 
[LOC China] had been trying to establish commercial relations with oil-producing nations such as [LOC Nigeria] as the [MISC Chinese] economy grows nearly 10 percent a year . 
Some officials have stated that [LOC Nigeria] hopes to sell communications bands to neighboring [MISC African] countries . 
[LOC Abuja] is the capital of [LOC Nigeria] . 
